"```sql\nSELECT d.forename, d.surname, MIN(lt.time) AS earliest_lap_time\nFROM drivers d\nJOIN lapTimes lt ON d.driverId = lt.driverId\nWHERE d.nationality = 'German'\n  AND d.dob BETWEEN '1980-01-01' AND '1990-12-31'\nGROUP BY d.driverId\nORDER BY earliest_lap_time\nLIMIT 3;\n```\n\nThis SQL query selects the forename and surname of German drivers who were born between 1980 and 1990, and it calculates the earliest lap time for each driver. The results are ordered by the earliest lap time, and only the top 3 drivers are returned."